   <text>
      <body>
         <div>
            <head>2.4.1885 Donnerstag</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="49025">Berlin</placeName>. April 2. 1885</p>
            <p>Went to the <name type="work" key="28832">Kaiser Panorama</name>. Photographs of
                  <placeName key="78805">America</placeName> and <placeName key="48900">Italy</placeName>
               <placeName key="49076">Australia</placeName> etc. Very interesting. Afterwards I
               again went to the <orgName key="68127">Museum</orgName>
               <note type="reg">Altes und
                  Neues Museum</note> and enjoyed the <name type="work" key="59415">Pergamum
                  sculptures</name> very much this time. Was struck by the beauty of the head of the
               woman who throws the vase with the serpent and of the head broken off a statue. I
               could sit hours and look at this last one. Also went to the <placeName key="66875">National Gallery</placeName> and saw and bought a photograph of <name type="work" key="81645">my favorite little sheperd</name> by <persName key="8405">Schlüter</persName>. Breakfasted at the same café<note type="reg">
                  <orgName key="81644">Café Unter den Linden</orgName>
               </note> we dined at the first day and
               then rushed so as to get the train for <placeName key="49069">Hamburg</placeName>
               where we arrived this evening.</p>
         </div>
